wikipedia rosalind brewer from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from rosalind g brewer jump to navigation search rosalind g brewer is an american businesswoman who is the former president and ceo of sams club a division of walmart stores inc on jan   walmart stores inc announced that she will retire from the role effective feb   and will be replaced by john furner she is the first woman and the first africanamerican to fill the role of ceo at one of walmart stores divisions as of  she is listed as the th most powerful woman in the world by forbes contents  early life and education  career  personal life  honors  references early life and educationedit brewer a detroit native attended cass technical high school in detroit she completed her undergraduate education at spelman college where she earned a bachelor’s degree in chemistry she is a graduate of the director’s college at the university of chicago booth school of businessstanford law school and she also attended an advanced management program at the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania careeredit brewer had a year career at kimberlyclark corporation starting out as a scientist she eventually advanced to president of the global nonwovens sector in  brewer’s career with walmart began in  with her position as regional vice president over operations in georgia from there she became the division president of walmart’s southeast market then president of walmart east in  brewer was named president and ceo of sam’s club becoming the first african american to lead a walmart division she has focused on health and wellness by doubling the amount of organic products offered at sams clubs brewer serves on the board of directors for lockheed martin corporation and is chair of the board of trustees for spelman on february   brewer was nominated for the starbucks board of directors brewer formerly served as a director of molson coors brewing co personal lifeedit brewer is married with two children honorsedit in  brewer was named one of the world’s  most powerful women by forbes the magazine also named her among the most powerful black women of  additionally working mother named her one of the most powerful working moms of  she has been honored by fortune magazine as one of the  most powerful women in business as of  she is listed as the th most powerful woman in the world by forbes fortune s most powerful women list of september   issue ranked brewer th in  she ranked th on fortunes annual ranking brewer received the spelman college legacy of leadership award referencesedit  a b c d rosalind brewer forbescom  retrieved    a b c rosalind brewer worlds most powerful women forbescom retrieved  august    a b c dead link  a b c d e f g h sams club rosalind brewer biography walmart retrieved  july    sams club ceo rosalind brewer to retire feb  drugstorenewscom retrieved    rosalind brewer named first woman africanamerican ceo of sams club huffington post  march  retrieved  september    a b the worlds  most powerful women forbes forbes retrieved february     rosalind brewer named first woman africanamerican ceo of sams club the huffington post january   retrieved october     a b bellstrom kristen september   fortunes most powerful women list fortune   starbucks nominates rosalind brewer to board of directors blavitycom retrieved    dead link  tricia griffith fortune  retrieved    rosalind brewer c spelmanedu retrieved   retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitlerosalindbreweroldid categories living peopleamerican women chief executivesamerican women business executivesamerican corporate directorswomen corporate directorsspelman college alumniuniversity of chicago booth school of business alumnistanford law school alumniwalmart peopleamerican retail chief executivesafricanamerican business executivesthcentury american businesspeoplestcentury american businesspeoplehidden categories all articles with dead external linksarticles with dead external links from july year