nt program at the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania careeredit brewer had a year career at kimberlyclark corporation starting out as a scientist she eventually advanced to president of the global nonwovens sector in  brewer’s career with walmart began in  with her position as regional vice president over operations in georgia from there she became the division president of walmart’s southeast market then president of walmart east in  brewer was named president and ceo of sam’s club becoming the first african american to lead a walmart division she has focused on health and wellness by doubling the amount of organic products offered at sams clubs brewer serves on the board of directors for lockheed martin corporation and is chair of the board of trustees for spelman on february   brewer was nominated for the starbucks board of directors brewer formerly served as a director of molson coors brewing co personal lifeedit brewer is married with two children honorsedit in  brewer was named one of the world’s  most powerful women by forbes the magazine also named her among the most powerful black women of  additionally working mother named her one of the most powerful working moms of  she has been honored by fortune magazine as one of the  most powerful women in business as of  she is listed as the th most powerful woman in the world by forbes fortune s most powerful women list of september   issue ranked brewer th in  she ranked th on fortunes annual ranking brewer received the spelman college legacy of leadership award referencesedit  a b c d rosalind brewer forbescom  retrieved    a b c rosalind brewer worlds most powerful women forbescom retrieved  august    a b c dead link  a b c d e f g h sams club rosalind brewer biography walmart retrieved  july    sams club ceo rosalind brewer to retire feb  drugstorenewscom retrieved    rosalind brewer named first woman africanamerican ceo of sams club huffington post  march  retrieved  september    a b the worlds  